1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,547
Once we have fixed our vocabulary, we can define the well-formed

2
00:00:03,647 --> 00:00:07,423
terms and well-formed formulas. This is somewhat similar to English.

3
00:00:07,466 --> 00:00:10,395
If we image the set of all possible combinations

4
00:00:10,495 --> 00:00:13,740
of letters in the alphabet, most will be meaningless.

5
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:17,986
However, some combinations of letters form words.

6
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:21,742
Here we define the terms recursively,

7
00:00:21,866 --> 00:00:23,248
where in the base case we say that the set

8
00:00:23,348 --> 00:00:25,188
of terms consists of: 1. All constants in the language,

9
00:00:25,266 --> 00:00:27,230
and 2. All variables in the language.

10
00:00:27,266 --> 00:00:32,288
Then if we have a function symbol F, which expects n-inputs, then given n

11
00:00:32,388 --> 00:00:36,779
terms t_1 through t_n, the term Ft_1 through t_n is also a term.

12
00:00:36,866 --> 00:00:39,224
So all of the following are examples

13
00:00:39,324 --> 00:00:41,886
of terms in the language of arithmetic.

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,463
Note that terms without variables, which are known as closed

15
00:00:45,563 --> 00:00:48,848
terms simply point to specific elements of the structure.

16
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:53,053
So in the theory of arithmetic, they simply point to numbers.

17
00:00:53,133 --> 00:00:55,360
Once we have our terms, we can combine them

18
00:00:55,460 --> 00:00:59,258
to create well-formed formulas. Similar to English, well-formed formulas

19
00:00:59,358 --> 00:01:02,777
are special combinations of terms that are grammatically correct.

20
00:01:02,866 --> 00:01:07,503
Again, these are defined recursively, where in the base case we have the

21
00:01:07,603 --> 00:01:11,778
relation terms, of the form: R t_1 through t_n, where R is n-ary.

22
00:01:11,866 --> 00:01:15,837
Note we are being general here, and most relations are binary. In

23
00:01:15,937 --> 00:01:19,845
form, these are the same as the functional terms, but instead of

24
00:01:19,945 --> 00:01:24,292
pointing to specific elements of the structure, they make a claim about

25
00:01:24,392 --> 00:01:27,048
the structure, which may or may not be true.

26
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:31,182
For example, the following are atomic formulas in the theory of arithmetic: 1+1=3.

27
00:01:31,282 --> 00:01:33,459
And 3 times 5 is less than 2 plus 8 times 12.

28
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:37,972
Then we can inductively define the non-atomic formulas using the Boolean

29
00:01:38,072 --> 00:01:41,818
connectives and the quantifiers. So if phi and psi are terms,

30
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:44,968
then so is phi and psi,

31
00:01:45,133 --> 00:01:49,578
so is for all x phi, etc.

32
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:53,768
Now we are ready to define what a mathematical structure is, and

33
00:01:53,868 --> 00:01:58,227
how we construct a bridge between the worlds of syntax and semantics.

